description:
Service Usage

The service will be used to register a Front End Loaded (FEL) Health Case from eMedical to the back-end system.
readme:
Service Usage

The service will be used to register a Front End Loaded (FEL) Health Case from eMedical to the back-end system.
This service will be used by CIC initially and will create details relating to the Health Case, Client details and Examinations.
It will also be used to update the back-end system of changes to the client's bio and contact details.

Service Behaviour

The back-end system will apply the advised changes to the relevant Health Case.
Note: This service is the only mechanism by which data that is collected in eMedical during the course of the medical examination is propagated to the back-end system. There is no intention for the examination data to remain in eMedical for historical purposes. Any element that is needed for historical purposes needs to be collected and sent to the back end system as part of this service.
Generally Asynchronous service, except when a Case is first managed by IOM, under which circumstance it is used Synchronously to interface to MiMOSA so that the user can become aware immediately of any failure.

Service Dependencies

XS019 is the externally dependent service that acts as a proxy for SV445.
No transform exists so the payload of SV445 is directly exposed via XS019 but in a flattened form.
